What is three tair architecture

Three tier = Web + App + DB — each in separate subnet with security groups allowing only necessary traffic between tiers! ✅

Simple Summary

"Three tier architecture separates the application into three layers — Presentation, Application, and Database. In AWS I implement this using public subnets for web servers behind an internet-facing ALB, private subnets for application servers behind an internal ALB, and another private subnet for RDS database. Each tier has its own security group — web tier accepts public traffic, app tier accepts only from web tier, and DB tier accepts only from app tier. This gives security, scalability, and high availability."

User opens browser
  → https://myapp.com
        ↓
Route 53 → ALB (public)
        ↓
Web Server (React)
  → serves HTML/CSS/JS
  → calls API
        ↓
Internal ALB
        ↓
App Server (Java/Python)
  → processes business logic
  → validates data
  → queries database
        ↓
RDS MySQL
  → stores/retrieves data
        ↓
Response flows back
to user ✅
